The White House sent three nominations to the Senate on June 24, 2009. James Legarde Hudson was nominated to be the United States Director of the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development. John Victor Roos was nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Japan. James B. Smith was nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.